HEADWORD: Excarnation
<hw>Ex`car*na"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of
depriving or divesting of flesh; excarnification; -- opposed to
<contr>incarnation</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

